race.comment: Tough race. BLUEPINOT (12) might be the one with more improvement to come third up from a spell. Two runs back have been good, boxing on well behind an in-form horse last time at Sale when ridden positively. Drawn for similar tactics here, he finds the right race and can break through. FIRST CHORUS (8) is a lightly raced mare who acquitted herself well in town last time at Sandown Hillside over 1600m. Back in trip is a slight query but she is fresh for it and will be hard to hold out. BRUNG KING (1) stuck on well fresh at Bendigo in this grade and should be fitter for it. Big weight again but gives a sight. SOME PEOPLE CALLME (6) resumes having only had one run last time in. His best form reads well for this and 1400m suits. Watch the betting. BRITISH POET (3) can improve.
